As a safeguard, stick to Airbnb terms and only send payments via its platform.Dubious characters lure clients to take this route, where they lose the digital protection and are likely to suffer. After a successful surgery in India, an elderly man was happy to return home on November 4, accompanied by his son. 

But on touching down at the Jomo Kenyatta International Airport, they learnt that a family member was down with Covid-19. This meant they could not proceed home in Lang’ata, Nairobi. 

A cousin, Michael Kibet, offered to help them find a house to stay for three nights. Mr Kibet logged into Airbnb, the online platform that links travellers and hosts, and reserved a house. So, they got into a taxi and headed for Garden Estate. 



