Her birthday was going to be lit! Her friend, an influencer too, was going to do a YouTube video about the place. The day before her birthday, she called to inquire about amenities available at the property. 

Her WhatsApp messages were getting two ticks but no responses. At one point, she could see the person was online and she tried calling but her calls were not picked. Her calls to the number she had made the M-Pesa payment to also went unanswered. She knew she had been conned. 

She moved to Instagram to see if any of her friends would know where to get the woman. One of her friends then told her that she was the second person to report having been scammed by the same woman. 

“He told me he had been following her, but she would DM him to ask for money so he stopped. He told me the other person scammed was Elodie Zone, who said it was on the exact house. They actually went there and found that no such house exists on Miotoni Road,” Wambui says. 



